Azure DevOps is Microsoft’s tool for managing the software development process.

Azure DevOps is a platform for planning work, collaborating on code, building apps, testing, and deploying to production


Azure DevOps helps developers take an idea and turn it into working software.

  Planning tasks
  
  Storing code
  
  Tracking bugs
  
  Building the project
  
  Testing the project
  
  Deploying the project online




The main parts of Azure DevOps

  Azure Boards

    This is for planning.

    It is like a project checklist for a team.

  
  Azure Repos
  
    Store your code, use Git, make branches, and track changes


  Azure Pipeline

    It automatically checks and publishes your code after you upload it

    It automates the stuff you would normally do by hand, like:

      Checking if the app has errors

      Making sure the app can run
      
      Running tests
      
      Uploading the app to the internet
              

  Azure Test Plans

    This is for testing.
    
    Teams use it to check if the app works correctly before releasing it.


  Azure Artifacts

    This is for storing packages and shared code tools.
    
    You probably do not need this first as a beginner.





